---
import '@fontsource/radley/400.css';
import '@fontsource/radley/400-italic.css';
import '../styles/source-figure.css';
import Shell from '../layouts/Shell.astro';

const tokens: [string, string][] = [
  ['medium', 'canvas + SVG'],
  ['ink', 'executed · #14161A'],
  ['blue', 'construction · #3656D4'],
  ['unit', '1ch × 21px'],
  ['studies', '7'],
  ['method', 'fn.toString()'],
];
---
<Shell title="Source / Figure" crumb="source · figure" tokens={tokens} wide
  description="Source / Figure — seven studies in self-referential notation, where each figure is drawn at runtime by the function printed beside it. A two-ink letterpress design study, retinted to the portfolio.">

  <div class="page-head">
    <span class="kicker">Design · study · self-referential notation</span>
    <h1 class="title">Source / Figure</h1>
    <p class="lede">Seven studies in which source code is the structure, texture, and rhythm of the image drawn from it. The code becomes the image.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="sf" transition:name="stage">
  <div class="sheet">

    <header class="intro">
      <div class="abstract">
        <p>Every figure on this sheet is drawn, at runtime, by the function printed beside it — and the printed text <em>is</em> the function: each source pane is <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:13px">Function.prototype.toString()</span>, read back from the object that did the drawing.</p>
        <p>Two inks are used. Black is execution: what ran, what printed. Non-photo blue is the pre-press pencil the camera cannot see: measures, construction lines, untaken branches, iterations already passed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="legend">
        <span><i class="sw ink"></i>INK — EXECUTED, PRINTS</span>
        <span><i class="sw blue"></i>NON-PHOTO BLUE — CONSTRUCTION, DOES NOT PRINT</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- =============== STUDY 01 =============== -->
    <section class="study" id="s1">
      <header class="s-head">
        <span class="s-no">Study 01 · Line</span>
        <h2>A line of code is a line</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="s-body cols">
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="pane-label">fn beams — Function.prototype.toString()</div>
          <pre id="src1"></pre>
          <div class="fnote">lines(fn) = fn.toString().split('\n') — the same rows drive both panes.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="pane-label">Fig. 1 — beams(beams, fig)</div>
          <div class="figwrap" id="fig1w"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="caption">Fig.&nbsp;1 is <b>beams</b> applied to itself: every printed line of the function becomes one beam — indentation for offset, character count for length. The beams begin in blue; as the program counter sweeps the source, each executed line receives its ink. Point at a beam and its line answers.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- =============== STUDY 02 =============== -->
    <section class="study" id="s2">
      <header class="s-head">
        <span class="s-no">Study 02 · Depth</span>
        <h2>Indentation is depth</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="s-body cols">
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="pane-label">fn profile — Function.prototype.toString()</div>
          <pre id="src2"></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="pane-label">Fig. 2 — profile(profile, fig)</div>
          <div class="figwrap" id="fig2w"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="caption">Read the left edge of any program and a terrain appears. <b>profile</b> traces its own margin: each row contributes its depth, the staircase is the scope structure, and the blue wash is the mass of nesting. Rows in the figure sit on the same 21-pixel rhythm as the rows of text.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- =============== STUDY 03 =============== -->
    <section class="study" id="s3">
      <header class="s-head">
        <span class="s-no">Study 03 · Containment</span>
        <h2>Brackets contain</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="s-body">
        <div class="cols">
          <div class="pane">
            <div class="pane-label">fn arcs — Function.prototype.toString()</div>
            <pre id="src3"></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="pane">
            <div class="pane-label">Fig. 3 — arcs(beams, fig) · scrolls →</div>
            <div class="scrollx"><div class="arcblock" id="fig3w"></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="caption"><b>arcs</b> flattens Study&nbsp;01 to a single line — a line of code owes you no line break — and draws a span for every matched pair. Containment becomes altitude: outer pairs arc higher, inner pairs shelter beneath them. The brackets themselves are set bold; they are the load-bearing glyphs.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- =============== STUDY 04 =============== -->
    <section class="study" id="s4">
      <header class="s-head">
        <span class="s-no">Study 04 · Repetition</span>
        <h2>A loop is a rhythm</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="s-body cols">
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="pane-label">fn unroll — Function.prototype.toString()</div>
          <pre id="src4"></pre>
          <div class="fnote">TURN = Math.PI / 16 — one sixteenth of a half turn per iteration.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="pane-label">Fig. 4 — unroll(fig) · the loop, unrolled</div>
          <div class="figwrap" id="fig4w"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="caption">One motif and a rule. The loop body prints eight times; each cell inks the current iteration and leaves the previous one in blue, so the rhythm of <b>i</b> is visible as motion. Superimposed at <b>Σ</b>, the cycle closes into a figure no single iteration contains.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- =============== STUDY 05 =============== -->
    <section class="study" id="s5">
      <header class="s-head">
        <span class="s-no">Study 05 · Choice</span>
        <h2>A condition forks</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="s-body cols">
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="pane-label">let sunlit; fn fork — Function.prototype.toString()</div>
          <pre id="src5"></pre>
          <button class="runbtn" id="forkbtn" type="button">sunlit = !sunlit; fork(fig)</button>
        </div>
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="pane-label">Fig. 5 — both branches exist; one executes</div>
          <div class="fork-fig">
            <div class="fork-panel">
              <svg id="figL" width="100%" viewBox="0 0 220 160" aria-label="consequent branch"></svg>
              <div class="fork-cap" id="capL">consequent — inked</div>
            </div>
            <div class="fork-panel">
              <svg id="figR" width="100%" viewBox="0 0 220 160" aria-label="alternate branch"></svg>
              <div class="fork-cap" id="capR">alternate — blue</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="caption">Both branches exist in the source, so both panels exist on the plate. Only the branch that executes receives ink; the alternate stays in non-photo blue, and its lines of source print blue with it. Flip the value and the ink changes sides. The blue panels are painted by the plate itself — code that does not run leaves no ink.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- =============== STUDY 06 =============== -->
    <section class="study" id="s6">
      <header class="s-head">
        <span class="s-no">Study 06 · Voice</span>
        <h2>Comments are the human hand</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="s-body">
        <div class="pane-label">fn execute — the program counter that swept Study 01</div>
        <div class="margins" id="margins">
          <pre id="src6"></pre>
          <div class="notes" id="notes6"></div>
          <svg class="leaders" id="leaders6" aria-hidden="true"></svg>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="caption"><b>execute</b> is the function that swept the program counter across Study&nbsp;01. Its machine text stays in the column; its comments step out into the margin, set in a human hand. Voice and instruction are different materials, and the typeface says so.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- =============== STUDY 07 =============== -->
    <section class="study" id="s7">
      <header class="s-head">
        <span class="s-no">Study 07 · Quine</span>
        <h2>Portrait of a function as itself</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="s-body">
        <div class="pane-label">fn portrait — the pane and the figure are the same characters</div>
        <div class="stage">
          <canvas id="cv7" aria-label="the source of portrait() interpolating between readable text and a spiral figure"></canvas>
          <div class="tbar">
            <span class="end">source</span>
            <input type="range" id="tslider" min="0" max="1000" value="0" step="1" aria-label="interpolation between source layout and figure layout">
            <span class="end">figure</span>
            <span class="tread" id="tread">t = 0.00</span>
            <button class="runbtn" id="loopbtn" type="button" aria-pressed="false" title="drive t back and forth between source and figure">loop</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="caption">The portrait's only material is its own text: <b>portrait.toString()</b>, placed character by character. At <b>t = 0</b> the canvas typesets the function and you can read it. At <b>t = 1</b> the same characters sit on a spiral and you can only see it. Every point between is both. The code does not describe the image; it becomes it.</p>
    </section>

    <footer class="colophon">
      <div class="row">
        <span>Source / Figure — Sheet no. 1</span>
        <span>Set in IBM Plex Mono &amp; Radley, inlined</span>
        <span>Plotted in ch × 21px</span>
      </div>
      <p>One theme only: this is a printed sheet, and non-photo blue does not survive inversion. Every figure above was drawn at runtime by the function shown beside it. View source — the page you are reading is the program that drew it.</p>
    </footer>

  </div>
  </div>
</Shell>

<script is:inline>
/* ============================================================
   The plate. Functions displayed on the sheet are defined at
   column zero so Function.prototype.toString() reads clean.
   ============================================================ */

function lines(fn) { return fn.toString().split('\n'); }

function beams(fn, fig) {
  const rows = lines(fn);
  for (let y = 0; y < rows.length; y++) {
    const line = rows[y];
    const indent = line.length - line.trimStart().length;
    const span = line.trim().length;
    if (span > 0) bar(fig, indent, y, span);
  }
}

function profile(fn, fig) {
  const rows = lines(fn), path = [];
  for (let y = 0; y < rows.length; y++) {
    const line = rows[y];
    if (line.trim().length === 0) continue;
    const depth = (line.length - line.trimStart().length) / 2;
    path.push([depth, y]);
  }
  steps(fig, path);
}

function arcs(fn, fig) {
  const flat = fn.toString().replace(/\s+/g, ' ');
  const open = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < flat.length; i++) {
    if ('([{'.includes(flat[i])) open.push(i);
    if (')]}'.includes(flat[i])) arch(fig, open.pop(), i, open.length);
  }
  return flat;
}

function unroll(fig) {
  for (let i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
    square(fig, cell(i), (i - 1) * TURN, 'blue');
    square(fig, cell(i), i * TURN, 'ink');
  }
  for (let k = 0; k < 8; k++) {
    square(fig, cell(8), k * TURN, k === 7 ? 'ink' : 'blue');
  }
}

let sunlit = true;

function fork(fig) {
  if (sunlit) {
    rings(fig.left, 'ink');
  } else {
    hatch(fig.right, 'ink');
  }
}

function execute(pre, step, ms) {
  // the program counter for this sheet
  const rows = pre.querySelectorAll('.ln');
  let k = 0;
  (function tick() {
    if (k > 0) rows[k - 1].classList.remove('pc');
    if (k === rows.length) return; // halt
    rows[k].classList.add('pc'); // ink the current line
    step(k);
    k = k + 1;
    setTimeout(tick, ms);
  })();
}

function portrait(cv, t) {
  const src = portrait.toString();
  const a = grid(src), b = spiral(src);
  const g = cv.getContext('2d');
  g.clearRect(0, 0, cv.width, cv.height);
  for (let i = 0; i < src.length; i++) {
    if (!a[i] || src[i] === ' ') continue;
    place(g, src[i], mix(a[i], b[i], ease(t)));
  }
}

/* ============================================================
   Below: the parts of the plate the studies reference.
   ============================================================ */

const NS = 'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg';
const INK = '#1A1815', BLUE = '#3656D4', BLUE_DEEP = '#3656D4', FAINT = '#E5E9FB', SOFT = '#6A635A';
const LH = 21, FS = 12.5;
const TURN = Math.PI / 16;
const RM = matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
let CH = 7.5, CH11 = 6.6;

const ease = t => 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3);

function el(name, attrs, parent) {
  const n = document.createElementNS(NS, name);
  for (const k in attrs) n.setAttribute(k, attrs[k]);
  if (parent) parent.appendChild(n);
  return n;
}

function esc(s) { return s.replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g, '&lt;'); }

function markup(codePart) {
  let h = esc(codePart);
  h = h.replace(/'[^']*'/g, m => '<span class="st">' + m + '</span>');
  h = h.replace(/\b(function|const|let|for|while|if|else|return|continue|of|new)\b/g, '<b>$1</b>');
  return h;
}

function highlight(code) {
  return code.split('\n').map(line => {
    const m = line.match(/^(.*?)(\/\/.*)$/);
    let h = m ? markup(m[1]) + '<span class="cm">' + esc(m[2]) + '</span>' : markup(line);
    return '<span class="ln">' + (h || ' ') + '</span>';
  }).join('');
}

function typeset(id, text) {
  document.getElementById(id).innerHTML = highlight(text);
}

/* ---- study 01 plate ---- */
let svg1 = null;
function bar(fig, indent, y, span) {
  el('rect', {
    x: (indent * CH).toFixed(1), y: y * LH + 5,
    width: (span * CH).toFixed(1), height: 9,
    class: 'beam', 'data-y': y
  }, fig);
}
function buildFig1() {
  const rows = lines(beams);
  const w = Math.max(...rows.map(r => r.length)) * CH + 6;
  const h = rows.length * LH;
  svg1 = el('svg', { width: Math.ceil(w), height: h, 'aria-label': 'each source line rendered as a beam' });
  for (let y = 0; y < rows.length; y++) {
    el('line', { x1: 0, y1: y * LH + 16.5, x2: Math.ceil(w), y2: y * LH + 16.5, class: 'baseline' }, svg1);
  }
  document.getElementById('fig1w').appendChild(svg1);
  beams(beams, svg1);
  // beam <-> line cross-highlight
  const pre = document.getElementById('src1');
  svg1.querySelectorAll('.beam').forEach(b => {
    const k = +b.getAttribute('data-y');
    b.addEventListener('pointerenter', () => pre.querySelectorAll('.ln')[k]?.classList.add('pc'));
    b.addEventListener('pointerleave', () => pre.querySelectorAll('.ln')[k]?.classList.remove('pc'));
  });
  if (RM) svg1.querySelectorAll('.beam').forEach(b => b.classList.add('on'));
}
function sweep1() {
  if (RM) return;
  svg1.querySelectorAll('.beam').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('on'));
  execute(document.getElementById('src1'), k => {
    const b = svg1.querySelector('[data-y="' + k + '"]');
    if (b) b.classList.add('on');
  }, 110);
}

/* ---- study 02 plate ---- */
let svg2 = null, path2 = null;
function steps(fig, pts) {
  const x = d => 30 + d * 7 * CH;
  const y = r => r * LH + 11.5;
  let d = 'M ' + x(pts[0][0]) + ' ' + y(pts[0][1]);
  let fill = 'M ' + x(0) + ' ' + y(pts[0][1]) + ' L ' + x(pts[0][0]) + ' ' + y(pts[0][1]);
  for (let i = 1; i < pts.length; i++) {
    d += ' V ' + y(pts[i][1]) + ' H ' + x(pts[i][0]);
    fill += ' V ' + y(pts[i][1]) + ' H ' + x(pts[i][0]);
  }
  fill += ' V ' + y(pts[pts.length - 1][1]) + ' H ' + x(0) + ' Z';
  el('path', { d: fill, fill: FAINT, stroke: 'none', class: 'terr' }, fig);
  path2 = el('path', { d: d, fill: 'none', stroke: INK, 'stroke-width': 1.8 }, fig);
}
function buildFig2() {
  const rows = lines(profile);
  const h = rows.length * LH;
  const w = 30 + 3 * 7 * CH + 64;
  svg2 = el('svg', { width: Math.ceil(w), height: h + 26, 'aria-label': 'indentation depth of each row as a step profile' });
  for (let d = 0; d <= 3; d++) {
    const gx = 30 + d * 7 * CH;
    el('line', { x1: gx, y1: 14, x2: gx, y2: h + 4, class: 'guide', 'stroke-dasharray': '1 4' }, svg2);
    const t = el('text', { x: gx - 2, y: 8, class: 'guide-label' }, svg2);
    t.textContent = d;
  }
  const lbl = el('text', { x: 30 + 3 * 7 * CH + 14, y: 8, class: 'guide-label' }, svg2);
  lbl.textContent = 'DEPTH';
  document.getElementById('fig2w').appendChild(svg2);
  profile(profile, svg2);
  const len = path2.getTotalLength();
  if (!RM) {
    path2.style.strokeDasharray = len;
    path2.style.strokeDashoffset = len;
    svg2.querySelector('.terr').style.opacity = 0;
  }
}
function draw2() {
  if (RM || !path2) return;
  path2.style.transition = 'stroke-dashoffset 1.4s cubic-bezier(.22,.61,.21,1)';
  path2.style.strokeDashoffset = 0;
  const t = svg2.querySelector('.terr');
  t.style.transition = 'opacity .9s ease-out .7s';
  t.style.opacity = 1;
}

/* ---- study 03 plate ---- */
let svg3 = null, arcpaths = [];
function arch(fig, a, b, depth) {
  const x1 = (a + 0.5) * CH11, x2 = (b + 0.5) * CH11;
  const h = Math.min(16 + (x2 - x1) * 0.22, 88);
  const p = el('path', {
    d: 'M ' + x1.toFixed(1) + ' 104 C ' + x1.toFixed(1) + ' ' + (104 - h).toFixed(1) +
       ' ' + x2.toFixed(1) + ' ' + (104 - h).toFixed(1) + ' ' + x2.toFixed(1) + ' 104',
    fill: 'none', stroke: INK, 'stroke-width': Math.max(0.7, 1.5 - depth * 0.2)
  }, fig);
  el('line', { x1: x1.toFixed(1), y1: 104, x2: x1.toFixed(1), y2: 110, stroke: BLUE, 'stroke-width': 1 }, fig);
  el('line', { x1: x2.toFixed(1), y1: 104, x2: x2.toFixed(1), y2: 110, stroke: BLUE, 'stroke-width': 1 }, fig);
  arcpaths.push(p);
}
function buildFig3() {
  const holder = document.getElementById('fig3w');
  const probe = arcs(beams, { appendChild: () => {} });
  // probe pass above only measured length via return; draw for real:
  const w = Math.ceil(probe.length * CH11) + 12;
  svg3 = el('svg', { width: w, height: 112, 'aria-label': 'bracket pairs of the flattened source drawn as arcs' });
  holder.appendChild(svg3);
  arcpaths = [];
  const flat = arcs(beams, svg3);
  const div = document.createElement('div');
  div.className = 'flat';
  div.innerHTML = esc(flat).replace(/([(){}[\]])/g, '<b>$1</b>');
  holder.appendChild(div);
  if (!RM) arcpaths.forEach(p => {
    const len = p.getTotalLength();
    p.style.strokeDasharray = len;
    p.style.strokeDashoffset = len;
  });
}
function draw3() {
  if (RM) return;
  arcpaths.forEach((p, i) => {
    p.style.transition = 'stroke-dashoffset .9s cubic-bezier(.22,.61,.21,1) ' + (i * 28) + 'ms';
    p.style.strokeDashoffset = 0;
  });
}

/* ---- study 04 plate ---- */
let svg4 = null;
function cell(i) { return 44 + i * 86; }
function square(fig, cx, a, ink) {
  const r = 17, pts = [];
  for (let q = 0; q < 4; q++) {
    const t = a + q * Math.PI / 2 + Math.PI / 4;
    pts.push((cx + r * 1.32 * Math.cos(t)).toFixed(1) + ',' + (58 + r * 1.32 * Math.sin(t)).toFixed(1));
  }
  const g = fig.querySelector('[data-cell="' + cx + '"]') || el('g', { 'data-cell': cx }, fig);
  el('polygon', {
    points: pts.join(' '), fill: 'none',
    stroke: ink === 'ink' ? INK : BLUE,
    'stroke-width': ink === 'ink' ? 1.7 : 1
  }, g);
}
function buildFig4() {
  const w4 = cell(8) + 52;
  svg4 = el('svg', { viewBox: '0 0 ' + w4 + ' 128', width: '100%', 'aria-label': 'eight iterations of a rotating square, then their superposition' });
  svg4.style.maxWidth = w4 + 'px';
  svg4.style.display = 'block';
  document.getElementById('fig4w').appendChild(svg4);
  unroll(svg4);
  for (let i = 0; i <= 8; i++) {
    const t = el('text', { x: cell(i), y: 118, 'text-anchor': 'middle', class: 'figtext', 'font-size': 13 }, svg4);
    t.textContent = i < 8 ? 'i=' + i : 'Σ';
  }
  if (!RM) svg4.querySelectorAll('[data-cell]').forEach((g, i) => {
    g.style.opacity = 0;
    g.style.transition = 'opacity .5s ease-out ' + (i * 100) + 'ms';
  });
}
function draw4() {
  svg4.querySelectorAll('[data-cell]').forEach(g => { g.style.opacity = 1; });
}

/* ---- study 05 plate ---- */
function rings(target, ink) {
  const g = el('g', { class: ink === 'ink' ? 'inkwork' : '' }, target);
  for (let k = 0; k < 6; k++) {
    const inset = 14 + k * 15;
    el('rect', {
      x: inset, y: inset * 160 / 220, width: 220 - 2 * inset, height: 160 - 2 * inset * 160 / 220,
      fill: 'none', stroke: ink === 'ink' ? INK : BLUE, 'stroke-width': ink === 'ink' ? 1.6 : 1
    }, g);
  }
  return g;
}
function hatch(target, ink) {
  const g = el('g', { class: ink === 'ink' ? 'inkwork' : '' }, target);
  for (let x = -160; x < 230; x += 13) {
    el('line', {
      x1: x, y1: 152, x2: x + 144, y2: 8,
      stroke: ink === 'ink' ? INK : BLUE, 'stroke-width': ink === 'ink' ? 1.4 : 1
    }, g);
  }
  el('rect', { x: 8, y: 8, width: 204, height: 144, fill: 'none', stroke: ink === 'ink' ? INK : BLUE, 'stroke-width': 1 }, g);
  return g;
}
const forkSrcId = 'src5';
function forkFrame() {
  const L = document.getElementById('figL'), R = document.getElementById('figR');
  // clip hatch lines to panel
  const defs = el('defs', {}, R);
  const cp = el('clipPath', { id: 'clipR' }, defs);
  el('rect', { x: 0, y: 0, width: 220, height: 160 }, cp);
  R.setAttribute('clip-path', 'url(#clipR)');
  rings(L, 'blue');
  hatch(R, 'blue');
  runFork(false);
}
function runFork(animate) {
  const L = document.getElementById('figL'), R = document.getElementById('figR');
  [L, R].forEach(s => s.querySelectorAll('.inkwork').forEach(n => n.remove()));
  fork({ left: L, right: R });
  const w = (sunlit ? L : R).querySelector('.inkwork');
  if (w && animate && !RM) {
    w.style.opacity = 0;
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      w.style.transition = 'opacity .45s ease-out';
      w.style.opacity = 1;
    });
  }
  // source: unexecuted lines print blue
  const rows = document.getElementById(forkSrcId).querySelectorAll('.ln');
  rows.forEach(r => {
    const t = r.textContent;
    const isRings = t.includes('rings(');
    const isHatch = t.includes('hatch(');
    if (isRings) r.classList.toggle('untaken', !sunlit);
    if (isHatch) r.classList.toggle('untaken', sunlit);
    if (t.includes('let sunlit')) { /* value token updated below */ }
  });
  const val = document.getElementById('sunval');
  if (val) val.textContent = String(sunlit);
  document.getElementById('capL').textContent = sunlit ? 'consequent — inked' : 'consequent — blue';
  document.getElementById('capR').textContent = sunlit ? 'alternate — blue' : 'alternate — inked';
}

/* ---- study 06 plate ---- */
function buildStudy6() {
  const raw = execute.toString().split('\n');
  const pre = document.getElementById('src6');
  const notesBox = document.getElementById('notes6');
  const found = [];
  const html = raw.map((line, row) => {
    const m = line.match(/^(.*?)\s*\/\/\s?(.*)$/);
    if (m) {
      found.push({ n: found.length + 1, text: m[2], row: row, chars: m[1].length });
      return '<span class="ln">' + markup(m[1]) + ' <sup class="mk">' + found.length + '</sup></span>';
    }
    return '<span class="ln">' + (markup(line) || ' ') + '</span>';
  }).join('');
  pre.innerHTML = html;
  notesBox.innerHTML = found.map(f =>
    '<div class="note" data-row="' + f.row + '" data-chars="' + f.chars + '"><span class="n">' + f.n + '</span>' + esc(f.text) + '</div>'
  ).join('');
  layoutNotes();
}
function layoutNotes() {
  const wrap = document.getElementById('margins');
  const pre = document.getElementById('src6');
  const svg = document.getElementById('leaders6');
  const notes = wrap.querySelectorAll('.note');
  if (getComputedStyle(svg).display === 'none') return;
  svg.innerHTML = '';
  svg.setAttribute('width', wrap.clientWidth);
  svg.setAttribute('height', wrap.clientHeight);
  const preTop = pre.offsetTop + 14; /* pre padding-top */
  const notesLeft = wrap.querySelector('.notes').offsetLeft;
  let lastBottom = 0;
  notes.forEach(note => {
    const row = +note.dataset.row, chars = +note.dataset.chars;
    const y = preTop + row * LH;
    const top = Math.max(y - 2, lastBottom + 6);
    note.style.top = top + 'px';
    lastBottom = top + note.offsetHeight;
    const x1 = pre.offsetLeft + Math.min(chars * CH + 26, pre.clientWidth - 4);
    el('line', {
      x1: x1.toFixed(1), y1: y + LH / 2,
      x2: notesLeft - 12, y2: top + 11
    }, svg);
  });
}

/* ---- study 07 plate ---- */
let cv7, ctx7, gridPos, spiralPos, boldFlag, W7, H7, tweenId = null;
function grid(src) {
  if (gridPos) return gridPos;
  const chC = CH * 12 / FS;
  const rows = src.split('\n');
  const maxc = Math.max(...rows.map(r => r.length));
  const ox = (W7 - maxc * chC) / 2, oy = (H7 - rows.length * 17) / 2 + 10;
  const out = [];
  let col = 0, row = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < src.length; i++) {
    if (src[i] === '\n') { out.push(null); row++; col = 0; continue; }
    out.push({ x: ox + col * chC, y: oy + row * 17, r: 0 });
    col++;
  }
  gridPos = out;
  return out;
}
function spiral(src) {
  if (spiralPos) return spiralPos;
  const chC = CH * 12 / FS;
  const cx = W7 / 2, cy = H7 / 2;
  const out = [];
  let r = 26, th = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < src.length; i++) {
    if (src[i] === '\n') { out.push(null); continue; }
    out.push({ x: cx + r * Math.cos(th), y: cy + r * Math.sin(th), r: th + Math.PI / 2 });
    const dth = (chC + 0.6) / r;
    th += dth;
    r += 15.5 * dth / (2 * Math.PI);
  }
  spiralPos = out;
  return out;
}
function mix(p, q, e) {
  if (!q) return p;
  return { x: p.x + (q.x - p.x) * e, y: p.y + (q.y - p.y) * e, r: p.r + (q.r - p.r) * e };
}
function place(g, chr, pos) {
  g.save();
  g.translate(pos.x, pos.y);
  g.rotate(pos.r);
  g.font = /[{}()[\]=+\-*/<>;.,:'!&|?]/.test(chr) ? '700 12px "IBM Plex Mono"' : '12px "IBM Plex Mono"';
  g.fillText(chr, 0, 0);
  g.restore();
}
function buildStudy7() {
  cv7 = document.getElementById('cv7');
  const holder = cv7.parentElement;
  W7 = Math.min(holder.clientWidth, 920);
  H7 = Math.min(560, Math.max(430, W7 * 0.62));
  const dpr = Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio || 1, 2);
  cv7.width = W7 * dpr; cv7.height = H7 * dpr;
  cv7.style.width = W7 + 'px'; cv7.style.height = H7 + 'px';
  ctx7 = cv7.getContext('2d');
  ctx7.setTransform(dpr, 0, 0, dpr, 0, 0);
  ctx7.fillStyle = INK;
  ctx7.textBaseline = 'middle';
  gridPos = null; spiralPos = null;
  const t0 = RM ? 1 : 0;
  setT(t0);
}
let t7 = 0, loop7 = null;
function setT(t) {
  t7 = t;
  document.getElementById('tslider').value = Math.round(t * 1000);
  document.getElementById('tread').textContent = 't = ' + t.toFixed(2);
  portrait(cv7, t);
}
function stopLoop() {
  if (loop7) cancelAnimationFrame(loop7);
  loop7 = null;
  const b = document.getElementById('loopbtn');
  b.textContent = 'loop';
  b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'false');
}
function startLoop() {
  const period = 9000;
  const phase = Math.acos(1 - 2 * Math.max(0, Math.min(1, t7))) / (2 * Math.PI) * period;
  const t0 = performance.now() - phase;
  const b = document.getElementById('loopbtn');
  b.textContent = 'halt';
  b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'true');
  (function step(now) {
    setT(0.5 - 0.5 * Math.cos((now - t0) / period * 2 * Math.PI));
    loop7 = requestAnimationFrame(step);
  })(performance.now());
}
function tween7() {
  if (RM || tweenId || loop7) return;
  const start = performance.now(), dur = 3200;
  function frame(now) {
    let u = Math.min(1, (now - start) / dur);
    u = u < .5 ? 4 * u * u * u : 1 - Math.pow(-2 * u + 2, 3) / 2;
    setT(u);
    if (u < 1) tweenId = requestAnimationFrame(frame);
    else tweenId = null;
  }
  tweenId = requestAnimationFrame(frame);
}

/* ============================================================
   Assembly.
   ============================================================ */

Promise.all([
  document.fonts.load('12.5px "IBM Plex Mono"'),
  document.fonts.load('700 12.5px "IBM Plex Mono"'),
  document.fonts.load('16px Radley'),
  document.fonts.load('italic 16px Radley')
]).then(() => document.fonts.ready).then(() => {
  // measure the sheet's units
  const mc = document.createElement('canvas').getContext('2d');
  mc.font = FS + 'px "IBM Plex Mono"';
  CH = mc.measureText('0000000000').width / 10;
  CH11 = CH * 11 / FS;

  // sources, verbatim from the objects that draw
  typeset('src1', beams.toString());
  typeset('src2', profile.toString());
  typeset('src3', arcs.toString());
  typeset('src4', unroll.toString());
  document.getElementById('src5').innerHTML =
    highlight('let sunlit = true;\n\n' + fork.toString())
      .replace(/\btrue\b/, '<span class="val" id="sunval" role="button" tabindex="0" title="flip the condition">true</span>');

  buildFig1();
  buildFig2();
  buildFig3();
  buildFig4();
  forkFrame();
  buildStudy6();
  buildStudy7();

  // interactions
  const flip = () => { sunlit = !sunlit; runFork(true); };
  document.getElementById('forkbtn').addEventListener('click', flip);
  document.getElementById('src5').addEventListener('click', e => {
    if (e.target.id === 'sunval') flip();
  });
  document.getElementById('src5').addEventListener('keydown', e => {
    if (e.target.id === 'sunval' && (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ')) { e.preventDefault(); flip(); }
  });
  document.getElementById('tslider').addEventListener('input', e => {
    if (tweenId) { cancelAnimationFrame(tweenId); tweenId = null; }
    stopLoop();
    setT(e.target.value / 1000);
  });
  document.getElementById('loopbtn').addEventListener('click', () => {
    if (loop7) { stopLoop(); return; }
    if (tweenId) { cancelAnimationFrame(tweenId); tweenId = null; }
    if (RM) { setT(t7 < 0.5 ? 1 : 0); return; }
    startLoop();
  });

  // motion on arrival
  const fired = new Set();
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
    entries.forEach(en => {
      if (!en.isIntersecting || fired.has(en.target.id)) return;
      fired.add(en.target.id);
      if (en.target.id === 's1') sweep1();
      if (en.target.id === 's2') draw2();
      if (en.target.id === 's3') draw3();
      if (en.target.id === 's4') draw4();
      if (en.target.id === 's7') tween7();
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.35 });
  ['s1', 's2', 's3', 's4', 's7'].forEach(id => io.observe(document.getElementById(id)));
  if (RM) draw4();

  let rsz = null;
  addEventListener('resize', () => {
    clearTimeout(rsz);
    rsz = setTimeout(() => { layoutNotes(); }, 120);
  });
});
</script>
